article.description:
Rolanda Monroe scored 17 points, and 
Southern University won the Southwestern Athletic Conference 
tournament Saturday with a 61-58 victory over Alabama State.
article.headline: Free-throw shooting helps Southern win SWAC title
article.linkText: Free-throw shooting helps Southern win SWAC's bid
article.story:
BIRMINGHAM, Ala. (AP) -- Rolanda Monroe scored 17 points, and 
Southern University won the Southwestern Athletic Conference 
tournament Saturday with a 61-58 victory over Alabama State.

Fredrieka Lewis added 16 points and teamed with Monroe to score 
23 of the Jaguars' final 24. Monroe scored the last 10 points from 
the foul line to hold off Alabama State's rally and help Southern
earn an automatic berth into the NCAA tournament.

Monroe was 13-for-13 from the free throw but made only two of 11
shots from the floor for Southern, which led 21-18 at halftime.

The Hornets tied it 46-46 at the six-minute mark on a 3-pointer by
Shantae Robinson. But Lewis anchored a 7-1 run to give Southern
(19-10) the lead for good.

Alabama State cut the deficit to one in the final minute, but
Monroe's clutch foul shooting kept Southern in front.

Tashia Holston scored 17 points to lead Alabama State (17-13),
and Robinson added 13 -- going 3-for-3 from behind the arc.

Southern shot 90 percent from the foul line in the second half
(20 of 22) and made 27 of 32 overall. Alabama State shot 36 percent
from the floor and converted 12 of 17 free throws.
